---
const operatingSystem = "Linux";
const quantity = 3;
const footwear = "boots";
const student = true;

const skillColor = "crimson";
---

<div class="relative min-h-screen bg-base-200">
	<main class="flex flex-col gap-12 px-4 pb-16 pt-10 lg:pt-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
		<section class="space-y-4 text-center">
			<p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-primary/70">Blog</p>
			<h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-extrabold">
				{operatingSystem} <span class="skill">{quantity}</span> {footwear}
			</h1>
			{student && <p class="text-base lg:text-lg text-base-content/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
				These posts are static for now. Later, you can swap them for content collections or data
				from your CMS or database.
			</p>}
		</section>

		<section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
			<article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
				<div class="card-body space-y-3">
					<span class="badge badge-outline badge-primary w-fit">Getting started</span>
					<h2 class="card-title text-xl">
						Welcome to your Astro + DaisyUI starter
					</h2>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
						Learn how this starter is wired with Tailwind 4, DaisyUI, and dark theme so you can
						focus on building content instead of configuration.
					</p>
					<div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs text-base-content/60">
						<span>5 min read</span>
						<span>Draft · Will be dynamic</span>
					</div>
					<div class="card-actions justify-start">
						<button class="btn btn-sm btn-primary">
							Read story
						</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
				<div class="card-body space-y-3">
					<span class="badge badge-outline badge-secondary w-fit">Design</span>
					<h2 class="card-title text-xl">
						Designing with DaisyUI components
					</h2>
					<p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
						Combine utility classes with DaisyUI’s component API to quickly sketch layouts,
						iterate on themes, and keep your styles consistent.
					</p>
					<div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs text-base-content/60">
						<span>7 min read</span>
						<span>Draft · Will be dynamic</span>
					</div>
					<div class="card-actions justify-start">
						<button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline btn-secondary">
							Read design tips
						</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="md:col-span-2 card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
				<div class="card-body space-y-3 lg:flex lg:items-center lg:gap-6">
					<div class="flex-1 space-y-3">
						<span class="badge badge-outline badge-accent w-fit">Changelog</span>
						<h2 class="card-title text-xl">
							What’s next: dynamic content & Supabase
						</h2>
						<p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
							This section will eventually be powered by real data. You can migrate these
							static cards to Astro content collections or load posts dynamically from
							Supabase.
						</p>
						<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-xs text-base-content/60">
							<span class="badge badge-ghost">Content collections</span>
							<span class="badge badge-ghost">Supabase</span>
							<span class="badge badge-ghost">Migrations</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="card-actions lg:flex-col lg:items-end lg:justify-between gap-3">
						<button class="btn btn-sm btn-accent">
							View roadmap
						</button>
						<button class="btn btn-sm btn-ghost">
							Coming soon
						</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</section>
	</main>
</div>

<style define:vars={{skillColor}}>
	.skill {
		color: green;
		color: var(--skillColor);
		font-weight: bold;
	}
</style>

